\ T81 shared-variable round-trip: store 42 into shared register 0, read it back,
\ GREEN if equal (RED if not).
\
\ The old version used `write-file`/`read-file` (0xd6/0xd7) with a guessed `value slot`
\ operand model and CRASHED the robot (stack underflow). Ground truth from OzoBlockly's
\ Dev-mode "store shared variable into [0]" block: it compiles to `42 0 set` (value,
\ register, `set` 0x93) -- the shared-variable registers are just low addresses reached
\ with the ordinary `set`/`get` ops, no file API. Load is the symmetric `0 get` (0x92).
evo
42 0 set
0 get 42 = if 0 127 0 led else 127 0 0 led then
forever 100 wait loop
